  "disclaimer": "Ransomware-readiness assessment: evidence and staged remediation recommendations only; not a readiness decision or attestation. No remediation has been executed and no assessment has been filed or closed.",
  "narrative": "Ransomware-readiness assessment of the wholesale-payments-platform scope as of 2026-07-15 (config rw-readiness-cfg-2026.07) evaluated eleven control gaps across the readiness domains and found ten fired. The most material concerns are on the tier-1 Wholesale Payments Core (SVC-PAY): it is not network-segmented, its backup is neither immutable nor offline, its last restore test was 409 days ago against a 180-day interval, and detection coverage is 0.72 against a 0.90 threshold. The Regulatory Reporting Hub (SVC-RPT) has no backup on record. Privileged accounts show 33 of 40 covered by MFA (0.82 against a required 1.00) with no administrative tiering. The most recent ransomware/IR exercise was 2024-11-01, beyond the 365-day interval, and the primary cloud host lacks resilience and recovery-commitment evidence. Six remediation recommendations are staged for a control owner to adjudicate; each is a candidate for approval, not an executed change. Suggested remediation-review priority: Elevated. Before prioritizing, weigh the review-context prompts (compensating controls, remediation already in flight, a planned decommission)."
}